Zach — if you ever find yourself in a situation again where you have mashed sweet potatoes that you want to turn into fries:
You could try piping them onto a silicon baking mat or parchment paper and then put them into the freezer
Once they’re frozen, try frying them
They may or may not maintain their shape ie they may break apart once it hits the fryer and may result in a hot mess and maybe some tears
I don’t know if A: it will work & B: if you would ever find yourself in this situation again (I haven’t tried it and if you do try it and it doesn’t work, I’m sorry in advance)
